╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 3.1: Delete and Change                ║
║  Category: Changes               Difficulty: ★☆☆ Fundamental    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  d     Delete selection (yanks to register)
  c     Change selection (delete + enter insert mode)
  Alt-d Delete selection WITHOUT yanking
  Alt-c Change selection WITHOUT yanking

The key insight: in Helix you SELECT first, then ACT.
  Vim:   dw  (delete word)
  Helix: wd  (select word, then delete)

  Vim:   cw  (change word)
  Helix: wc  (select word, then change)

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Replace each animal name with the replacement shown in parens.
  Use w to select the word, then c to change it.

  After pressing c, you'll enter insert mode — type the new word,
  then press Esc to return to normal mode.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

The cat (dog) sat on the mat.
A horse (zebra) galloped across the field.
The eagle (hawk) soared above the mountains.
A dolphin (whale) swam through the ocean.

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

The dog sat on the mat.
A zebra galloped across the field.
The hawk soared above the mountains.
A whale swam through the ocean.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Move to "cat", press w to select it, then c.
  Hint 2: You're now in insert mode. Type "dog" then Esc.
  Hint 3: Now delete the hint text " (dog)" — select it and d.
  Hint 4: Repeat for each line. Remember: w c <type> Esc is
          the core pattern for "change a word" in Helix.
